==National High School Hall of Fame==

The National High School Hall of Fame is a program of the National Federation of State High School Associations that honors individuals who have made outstanding contributions to high school sports or performing arts. Since 1986, the Hall of Fame enshrinement ceremony has been the final event of the National Federation&#x27;s annual summer meeting, which is held in late June and early July and attended by board members and executives of the state high school associations.

